HEADWORD: Gobemouche
<hw>Gobe`mouche"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<def>Literally, a fly swallower; hence, once who keeps his mouth open; a
boor; a silly and credulous person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

